Description: Limestone ostracon: on one side only, fourteen lines of a business text containing a list of articles taken to the prospective bride's(?) house by an unnamed man who was rejected for a second time. Line 2 has been cancelled in red.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: J. J. Černy and A.H. Gardiner, ‘Hieratic Ostraca’ (Oxford, 1957), p. 16 and pl. LVI, 1; S. Allam, 'Hieratische Ostraka und Papyri aus der Ramessidenzeit' (Tubingen, 1973), no. 222, pp. 222-3; A.G. McDowell, 'Village Life in Ancient Egypt '(Oxford, 1999), pp. 45-6, no. 20.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136399) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136399)
Condition: fair (chipped). The text is somewhat faded.
